kbdd - kbd daemon
===================
simple daemon and library to make per window layout
using XKB(X KeyBoard Extension).

Features:
  * dbus interface
  * set layout group by its number
  * switch to the previous layout 

Requirements
------------
In order to build kbdd you need:
 * xorg header files with xkb support
 * glib header files 
 * dbus-glib header files (optional) 

Installation
------------
Program uses autotools installation system, so installation
can be done in next steps:

  ./configure options
  make 
  make install

configuration options:
  debug - adds additional debuging info
  dbus  - enable dbus support

Running kbdd
-----------
to run kbdd you can just run /usr/bin/kbdd to use kbdd in deamon
mode, or '/usr/bin/kbdd -n' to run in verbose mode.

More info
---------------
you can go to kbdd wiki to check usecases described:
http://github.com/qnikst/kbdd/wiki/Usecases

Troubleshooting
---------------
All bugs and issues can be posted to 
http://github.com/qnikst/kbdd/issues
or sent to 
jabber: qnikst@gentoo.ru

